news.title: Kolkata: Drainage approval must for buildings sanction along EM Bypass
news.para: Though this rule will also be applicable for construction of housing projects in the city proper, the civic body has decided to keep a special vigil on areas off Bypass, including Nayabad, Mukundapur and Panchasayar, and other added areas such as Behala and Joka.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet gives nine months more for housing societies to hold AGMs
news.para: The extension was recommended by the state cooperatives commissioner, citing that only 20% societies had their audits and budgets ready due to Covid restrictions that were in place till August 31.

news.title: HDFC sells part of invoked shares of Ansal Housing to recover dues
news.para: In August, HDFC had invoked 46,20,000 shares of Ansal Housing Limited (Ansal) aggregating 7.78 per cent of the paid-up share capital, for recovery of part outstanding dues against loans availed by pledgers/borrowers.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM announces plots for poor people without homes
news.para: Under the scheme, poor people who do not have a place to live, will be provided with a plot. In cities where land is not available, multi-story buildings will be constructed. Land freed from the mafia will be used to build housing for the poor.

news.title: With no town planning, Secunderabad cantonment board fails to push back squatters
news.para: In the absence of such a wing — unlike the Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation — there is no dedicated team to check illegal constructions or encroachments in the cantonment area.

news.title: Twelve years on, Karnataka's rainwater harvesting dream stuck in pipeline
news.para: What’s more worrying is that of these two lakh properties, 80% are not making use of the harvested water. They continue to depend on Cauvery and underground water for all purposes, defeating the very purpose of RWH installation.

news.title: Telangana: GO 111 land now hot real estate destinations
news.para: Markets indicate land prices have, parallelly, shot by over 50% to touch Rs 2 crore per acre (approx) on an average. ​​In Shankerpally, the rates are higher --- anywhere between Rs 3 and 5 crore per acre. A sizeable part of this locality too is covered by GO 111.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP sets up panel for takeover of Ardee City
news.para: DTCP has formed a five-member committee under the chairmanship of the senior town planner. Residents have welcomed the move and said they hope it will help in resolving civic issues of the society.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body identifies three areas for MIG layouts
news.para: Visakhapatnam Metropolitan Region Development Authority (VMRDA) has identified three land parcels, measuring 363 acres in the district, for developing MIG (middle-income group) plots.

news.title: Chandigarh: Over Rs 10 lakh material can be bought for construction waste plant
news.para: The move comes at a time when the civic body is planning to mechanise the C&D waste plant with full automatic technology to enhance its capacity to increase productivity.

news.title: Resumption of sand mining to bring much-needed relief: Bihar minister
news.para: The minister told this reporter on Saturday that the department was planning to monitor the mining ghats through drone cameras, but the government had not given its permission yet.

news.title: Gurugram: Ansal Fernhill buyers protest over 11-year delay in flat handover
news.para: Around 70 homebuyers, along with women, children and senior citizens, gathered at the project site in the morning, holding posters and raising slogans against the developer for failing to complete the project even 11 years after its launch.

news.title: HC stays auction of 18 more acres at Puppalaguda, Telangana govt moves SC
news.para: The state government has decided to challenge the stay orders in Supreme Court. The Telangana State Industrial Infrastructure Corporation (TSIIC) has scheduled the auction of the 95 acres on September 28, which is now in jeopardy.

news.title: Stop fresh constructions outside lal dora in villages: Punjab governor
news.para: Recently, the administration had asked the Indian Institute of Human Settlements (IIHS), Bengaluru, to submit a revised draft policy on village development, regularisation of illegal structures and extension of lal dora.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body receives 7,766 applications under TS-bPASS
news.para: Among all the applications received so far, 6439 applications have been filed under the instant approval category out of which 4,071 applications were accepted, 1,423 rejected and 945 are under process.
